{"id":6813,"date":"2023-07-17T10:29:55","date_gmt":"2023-07-17T10:29:55","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/klimacontra.com\/?post_type=dt_portfolio&#038;p=6813"},"modified":"2024-12-23T09:44:16","modified_gmt":"2024-12-23T09:44:16","slug":"cav-kc-cav","status":"publish","type":"dt_portfolio","link":"https:\/\/klimacontra.com\/products\/cav-kc-cav\/","title":{"rendered":"CAV &#8211; KC CAV C"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>[vc_row][vc_column width=&#8221;1\/3&#8243;][vc_single_image image=&#8221;10841&#8243; img_size=&#8221;650&#215;650&#8243;][\/vc_column][vc_column width=&#8221;2\/3&#8243;][vc_column_text]<\/p>\n<h4><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; color: #000000;\"><strong>Klimacontra Constant Air Volume regulators<\/strong> <\/span><\/h4>\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>CAV &#8211; KC CAV C Constant Air Volume regulators<\/strong> facilitate automatic air flow control, assisting in the regulation and maintenance of a constant air volume flow in the ventilation system.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">The role for<strong> Klimacontra Constant Air Volume regulators<\/strong> is to maintain and keep a constant air flow volume while operating automatically.<\/span><\/p>\n<div class=\"ProductDetailsImageEU row\">\n<div id=\"ProductDetailsRightEU\" class=\"ProductDetailsRightEU col-lg-12 col-md-12 col-sm-12 col-xs-12 prdet-rght\">\n<div id=\"BackgroundDetailInfoEU\" data-read-more=\"{ visible: false, useStyledContainer: false }\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Volume flow controllers play a crucial role in complex piping systems by automatically controlling the distribution of air, ensuring precise management of air amounts.<\/span><\/div>\n<div data-read-more=\"{ visible: false, useStyledContainer: false }\"><\/div>\n<div data-read-more=\"{ visible: false, useStyledContainer: false }\">\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Air volume regulator<\/strong> constitute an independent regulation element, working without an external energy supply. It provides stable, required volume of air, irrespectively of the changes of the pressures in the system, leading to a total elimination of the need of counterbalancing the system.<\/span><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n<div data-read-more=\"{ visible: false, useStyledContainer: false }\">\n<div class=\"row\">\n<div class=\"column small-12\">\n<article id=\"product-1393\" class=\"single-product-content post-1393 product type-product status-publish has-post-thumbnail product_cat-air-pressure-regulators product_cat-constant-air-volume-regulators-cav product_tag-air-distribution-systems first instock product-type-simple\">\n<div class=\"row\">\n<div class=\"column medium-12 large-7 large-pull-5\">\n<h4><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; color: #000000;\"><strong>Constant Air Volume regulators <\/strong><\/span><\/h4>\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Constant Air Volume regulators <\/strong>can be used in inflow and outflow systems, high or low pressure in the vertical or horizontal position. <\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">CAV s can also work reliably from the minimum difference of pressures, which depends on the velocity of the air .<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">The usage of <strong>CAV<\/strong> s is important worldwide especially when obstacles arise when trying to keep a building warmer or cooler than the outside temperature. <\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">The aim of the <strong>HVAC system<\/strong> is to keep the buildings\u2019 inhabitants comfortable and healthy while considering system and equipment costs. <\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">When designing and installing high rise, multi-floor, data centers, hospitals or even commercial centers supply and exhaust systems, balancing can become an issue.\u00a0 Fan pressures and thermal stack effects can cause differences in how much supply\/exhaust air each floor experiences. \u00a0<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">When spaces experience the incorrect amount of supply\/exhaust air it can affect the humidity, air quality, and cost to condition the space. <\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Klimacontra Constant Air Volume Regulators<\/strong> (CAVs) are a simple solution to overcome these obstacles. <\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">These cost efficient small devices automatically control the passage of air without the use any electric controls or sensors, making them a cost-effective and a perfect solution to handle both intake and exhaust applications with no extra attachments or changes. Without the need for \u00a0controllers or sensors, easy installation, and minimal maintenance,\u00a0 <strong>Klimacontra Constant Air Volume Regulators<\/strong> (CAVs)\u00a0 are a cost-effective solution when compared other methods. <\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">You can install the CAVs after construction as well.<\/span><\/p>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/article>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<p>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column][\/vc_row]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>[vc_row][vc_column width=&#8221;1\/3&#8243;][vc_single_image image=&#8221;10841&#8243; img_size=&#8221;650&#215;650&#8243;][\/vc_column][vc_column width=&#8221;2\/3&#8243;][vc_column_text] Klimacontra Constant Air Volume regulators CAV &#8211; KC CAV C Constant Air Volume regulators facilitate automatic air flow control, assisting in the regulation and maintenance of a constant air volume flow in the ventilation system. The role for Klimacontra Constant Air Volume regulators is to maintain and keep a constant&hellip;<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":10841,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","template":"","dt_portfolio_category":[118],"dt_portfolio_tags":[],"class_list":["post-6813","dt_portfolio","type-dt_portfolio","status-publish","has-post-thumbnail","hentry","dt_portfolio_category-duct